sentences: Philip Creswick (born 12 October 1965, Charlwood, Surrey, England) is an English musician and songwriter, and a former member of the boy band, Big Fun.
He was then a backing vocalist in the boy band, Big Fun, which was active between 1989 and 1994.
Their album, A Pocketful of Dreams, reached number 7 in the UK charts in 1990, while their cover of The Jacksons' "Blame It on the Boogie" reached number 4 in the singles charts.

Creswick's later songwriting credits include: Family Fantastic's album Nice (2000, in collaboration with Jason Creasey and Vince Clarke) and the soundtrack to Winning London (2001, in collaboration with Nigel Lewis and Vince Clarke).
